{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"zettel.20260420092900","title":"Enterprise architects lebih efektif ketika ikut masuk ke tim pengembangan","desc":"Fowler: EA group yang terpisah dari pengembangan harian kehilangan konteks dan perspektif perusahaan; dekat ke tim lebih efektif.","tags":["permanent-note","software-architecture","enterprise-architecture","governance","martin-fowler"],"custom":{},"fname":"zettel.20260420092900","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"9aeab29ae640b38da6a99fac508825e0","updated":1776683200438,"created":1776683200438,"links":[{"type":"frontmatterTag","from":{"fname":"zettel.20260420092900","id":"zettel.20260420092900","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"tags.permanent-note","alias":"permanent-note","xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"tags.permanent-note"}},{"type":"frontmatterTag","from":{"fname":"zettel.20260420092900","id":"zettel.20260420092900","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"tags.software-architecture","alias":"software-architecture","xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"tags.software-architecture"}},{"type":"frontmatterTag","from":{"fname":"zettel.20260420092900","id":"zettel.20260420092900","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"tags.enterprise-architecture","alias":"enterprise-architecture","xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"tags.enterprise-architecture"}},{"type":"frontmatterTag","from":{"fname":"zettel.20260420092900","id":"zettel.20260420092900","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"tags.governance","alias":"governance","xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"tags.governance"}},{"type":"frontmatterTag","from":{"fname":"zettel.20260420092900","id":"zettel.20260420092900","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"tags.martin-fowler","alias":"martin-fowler","xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"tags.martin-fowler"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"zettel.20260420092900","id":"zettel.20260420092900","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"zettel.literature.software-architecture-guide","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":3,"offset":1030},"end":{"line":20,"column":52,"offset":1079},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"zettel.literature.software-architecture-guide"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"zettel.20260420092900","id":"zettel.20260420092900","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"zettel.20260420092009","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":3,"offset":1082},"end":{"line":21,"column":28,"offset":1107},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"zettel.20260420092009"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"zettel.20260420092900","id":"zettel.20260420092900","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"zettel.20260420092459","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":3,"offset":1172},"end":{"line":22,"column":28,"offset":1197},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"zettel.20260420092459"}},{"from":{"fname":"zettel","id":"zettel","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":48,"column":3,"offset":3569},"end":{"line":48,"column":28,"offset":3594},"indent":[]},"value":"zettel.20260420092900"},{"from":{"fname":"zettel.moc.software-architecture","id":"zettel.moc.software-architecture","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":55,"column":3,"offset":3734},"end":{"line":55,"column":28,"offset":3759},"indent":[]},"value":"zettel.20260420092900"}],"anchors":{},"children":[],"parent":"zettel","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"enterprise-architects-lebih-efektif-ketika-ikut-masuk-ke-tim-pengembangan\">Enterprise architects lebih efektif ketika ikut masuk ke tim pengembangan<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#enterprise-architects-lebih-efektif-ketika-ikut-masuk-ke-tim-pengembangan\"></a></h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Enterprise Architecture groups often get separated from day to day development. This can lead to their knowledge of development work getting out of date and development teams not taking a broad company-wide perspective. Having seen this happen frequently my colleague (Thoughtworks CTO) Rebecca argues that enterprise architects can be much more effective by joining development teams.</p>\n<p>Sumber: <a href=\"https://martinfowler.com/architecture/\">https://martinfowler.com/architecture/</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Catatan gue:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>EA group sering terpisah dari pekerjaan pengembangan harian.</li>\n<li>Akibatnya, pengetahuan mereka tentang kerja development jadi basi dan tim kehilangan perspektif perusahaan.</li>\n<li>Solusinya adalah enterprise architects ikut masuk ke tim pengembangan.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Implikasi:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Ini menghubungkan kembali kritik awal Fowler terhadap arsitektur yang terpisah dari programming.</li>\n<li>Level enterprise pun perlu arsitektur dekat dengan kerja nyata, bukan hanya dokumen atau framework terpisah.</li>\n<li>Enterprise architect efektif ketika menjadi bagian dari tim, bukan sekadar pengawas jauh.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Hubungan:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.literature.software-architecture-guide\">Software Architecture Guide — Fowler: arsitektur sebagai keputusan penting dan mahal kalau salah</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.20260420092009\">Sentralisasi total di EA melambatkan keputusan dan kehilangan konteks lokal</a> — kritik terhadap sentralisasi total sebagai model governance</li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.20260420092459\">Otonomi tanpa koordinasi di EA berubah jadi fragmentasi mahal</a> — risiko otonomi tanpa koordinasi</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"tags\">Tags<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#tags\"></a></h2>\n<ol>\n<li><a title=\"Private\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"private\">permanent-note (Private)</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"Private\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"private\">software-architecture (Private)</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"Private\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"private\">enterprise-architecture (Private)</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"Private\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"private\">governance (Private)</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"Private\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"private\">martin-fowler (Private)</a></li>\n</ol>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel\">Zettelkasten</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.moc.software-architecture\">MOC: Software Architecture</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"root","title":"Hello and Welcome! 👋","desc":"","updated":1742030256619,"created":1646842475821,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"453f88f4a5f1ad7629ebb7cc49502125","links":[],"anchors":{"find-more":{"type":"header","text":"Find More","value":"find-more","line":20,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["book-summaries","daily","handbook","notes","tags","til","zettel"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"\nWelcome to the homepage! I use Dendron to store and organize notes, ideas, and experiments I’m working on. Here are the main sections you’ll find on this site:\n\n1. **Learning Notes** — Practical notes on programming, recent technologies, and productivity tips.\n2. **Personal Projects** — Summaries of projects, experiments, and outcomes I’m working on or have completed.\n3. **Writings & Opinions** — Casual articles and reflections about technology, daily life, and other interesting topics.\n\nI’m constantly experimenting and learning. I hope the content here helps you as a reference, a starting point for discussion, or just light reading.\n\n> Why Dendron?\n>\nDendron helps keep notes organized. Its \"seed\" and \"vault\" concepts make it easy to structure content and find what you need.\n\n## Find More\n\nIf you want to learn more or connect, check these links:\n\n- [Homepage (Dendron)](https://zeihanaulia.github.io/sotoy/)\n- [My GitHub](https://github.com/zeihanaulia)\n- [My Twitter / X](https://x.com/zeihanaulia)\n\nThanks for stopping by. If you have feedback or want to chat, feel free to reach out.\n"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":5,"dev":{"enablePreviewV2":true},"commands":{"lookup":{"note":{"selectionMode":"extract","confirmVaultOnCreate":true,"vaultSelectionModeOnCreate":"smart","leaveTrace":false,"bubbleUpCreateNew":true,"fuzzThreshold":0.2}},"randomNote":{},"insertNoteLink":{"aliasMode":"none","enableMultiSelect":false},"insertNoteIndex":{"enableMarker":false},"copyNoteLink":{"aliasMode":"title"},"templateHierarchy":"template"},"workspace":{"dendronVersion":"0.83.0","vaults":[{"fsPath":"vault"}],"journal":{"dailyDomain":"daily","name":"journal","dateFormat":"y.MM.dd","addBehavior":"childOfDomain"},"scratch":{"name":"scratch","dateFormat":"y.MM.dd.HHmmss","addBehavior":"asOwnDomain"},"task":{"name":"","dateFormat":"","addBehavior":"childOfCurrent","statusSymbols":{"":" ","wip":"w","done":"x","assigned":"a","moved":"m","blocked":"b","delegated":"l","dropped":"d","pending":"y"},"prioritySymbols":{"H":"high","M":"medium","L":"low"},"todoIntegration":false,"createTaskSelectionType":"selection2link","taskCompleteStatus":["done","x"]},"graph":{"zoomSpeed":1,"createStub":false},"enableAutoCreateOnDefinition":false,"enableXVaultWikiLink":false,"enableRemoteVaultInit":true,"enableUserTags":true,"enableHashTags":true,"workspaceVaultSyncMode":"noCommit","enableAutoFoldFrontmatter":false,"enableEditorDecorations":true,"maxPreviewsCached":10,"maxNoteLength":204800,"seeds":{"dendron.templates":{}},"enableFullHierarchyNoteTitle":false},"preview":{"enableFMTitle":true,"enableNoteTitleForLink":true,"enableFrontmatterTags":true,"enableHashesForFMTags":false,"enablePrettyRefs":true,"enableKatex":true,"automaticallyShowPreview":false},"publishing":{"enableFMTitle":true,"enableNoteTitleForLink":true,"enablePrettyRefs":true,"enableKatex":true,"copyAssets":true,"siteHierarchies":["root"],"wr